typing in japanese on iphone?
by TheEnglishKnitter » Wed 04.20.2011 2:42 pm I am a complete technology novice so I need some real step by step help.I have downloaded an app called iflash free, an app where I can create my own Q&A flashcards.I need to be able to type, initially (because I am just starting) in romaji with the 'microns', but soon in hiragana and katakana and eventually in kanji.How do I bring up a japanese keyboard in romaji/ hiragana/ katakana or kanji?The EnglishKnitter
